{"author":{"id":"ae924cad0eccd510bd7c1844896b3dcc00e7daa039003bd9719a515e70528ab9"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1761768074,"nonce":"rnAiQ/VU1/Vgz1ifqeE0KSjJe68=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s7Upgka","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/7414","origin":"github"},"title":"Projection workflow for generating MAFs from cactus alignments","message":"## Description\n\nMAF files from Cactus alignments need to be projected onto a specific reference genome before analysis. Need to add a preliminary workflow step to handle this projection.\n\n## Background\n\nFrom the meeting discussion (Oct 24, 2025):\n\n**Anton Nekrutenko:**\n\u003e \"Asked about differences between MAF files generated by cactus and multisz, and the need for a MAF file to be associated with a reference.\"\n\n**Maximilian Haeussler:**\n\u003e \"MAF files are reference-projected and single-coverage, explaining that a single HAL file is too slow, so a separate MAF file is extracted for each reference species.\"\n\n## The Challenge\n\n1. **Cactus generates HAL files** - These contain all pairwise alignments but are too slow for direct analysis\n2. **MAF extraction needed** - Must extract MAF for specific reference\n3. **User must specify reference** - Workflow needs to ask which species is the reference\n4. **Multiple MAFs possible** - May need MAF for multiple reference perspectives\n\n## Current Workflow Gap\n\n```\nCactus Alignment → HAL file → ??? → MAF file → MAF analysis tools\n                           (missing step)\n```\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n```\nCactus Alignment → HAL file → HAL-to-MAF tool → MAF file → MAF analysis tools\n                           (select reference)\n```\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Tool Development\n\n- [ ] Wrap hal2maf or equivalent tool for Galaxy\n- [ ] Add reference genome selection parameter\n- [ ] Support batch extraction (multiple reference MAFs)\n- [ ] Handle large HAL files efficiently\n- [ ] Add progress reporting for long conversions\n\n### Workflow Creation\n\n- [ ] Create \"HAL to MAF Projection\" workflow\n- [ ] Add reference selection interface\n- [ ] Include validation steps\n- [ ] Document expected input/output formats\n- [ ] Provide example HAL files for testing\n\n### Documentation\n\n- [ ] Explain MAF reference-projection concept\n- [ ] Document when projection is needed\n- [ ] Provide guidance on reference selection\n- [ ] Include troubleshooting for common issues\n- [ ] Add examples with Cactus alignments\n\n### Testing\n\n- [ ] Test with small Cactus HAL files\n- [ ] Test with multi-species alignments\n- [ ] Verify MAF format correctness\n- [ ] Test integration with downstream MAF tools\n- [ ] Performance benchmarking\n\n## Cactus Tools Available\n\nResearch which tools to use:\n- hal2maf (from Cactus suite)\n- halStats (for HAL inspection)\n- Other relevant Cactus utilities\n\n## User Experience\n\nThe workflow should:\n1. Accept HAL file input\n2. Display available species/genomes\n3. Allow user to select reference\n4. Extract MAF projected to that reference\n5. Validate output MAF\n6. Pass to downstream analysis\n\n## Example Use Case\n\n**VGP Scenario:**\n1. User runs progressive Cactus on 10 bird genomes\n2. Receives HAL file with all alignments\n3. Wants to analyze conserved regions in chicken\n4. Selects chicken as reference → extracts chicken-referenced MAF\n5. Runs mafCoverage, mafGene, etc. on chicken MAF\n\n## References\n\n- Meeting notes: Oct 24, 2025, discussion starting at 00:23:03\n- Cactus documentation: https://github.com/ComparativeGenomicsToolkit/cactus\n- HAL format: https://github.com/ComparativeGenomicsToolkit/hal","files":null}]}